COMMENT.comment_text: Easy access to info, added in libpng-0.99
The following casts work because a PNG 4 byte integer only has a valid * range of 0..2^31-1; otherwise the cast might overflow.
The argument is a PNG unsigned integer, so it is not permitted * to be bigger than 2^31.

Convert from meters * 1,000,000 to inches * 100,000, meters to * inches is simply *(100/2.54), so we want *(10/2.54) == 500/127. * Notice that this can overflow - a warning is output and 0 is * returned.
To avoid the overflow do the conversion directly in floating * point.
To avoid the overflow do the conversion directly in floating * point.

The XYZ APIs were added in 1.5.5 to take advantage of the code added at the * same time to correct the rgb grayscale coefficient defaults obtained from the * cHRM chunk in 1.5.4

Quiet API change: this code used to only return the end points if a cHRM * chunk was present, but the end points can also come from iCCP or sRGB * chunks, so in 1.6.0 the png_get_ APIs return the end points regardless and * the png_set_ APIs merely check that set end points are mutually * consistent.
